text.autoconfig.fuzzy.title: Fuzzy Configuration
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.fuzzySearch: Only shows fuzzy search results with a score higher than or equal to the set threshold, indicating a close match to the search term.
Defines the maximum number of results returned from a fuzzy search.
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.clearOnJoin: Automatically clears previous commands when switching the server.
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.showScore.@: Displays the relevancy score of each result in fuzzy searches. The higher the number, the more closely the result matches your search query.
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.enableShift: Enables the ability to perform actions on the selected command by holding shift and pressing the corresponding key.
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.enableComma: If enabled, logs the commands from command blocks when you update them.
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.ignoredComm: Comma-Separated list of ignored command prefixes (without leading slash, e. g. 'msg ')
text.autoconfig.fuzzy.option.loadCommand: If enabled, loads the command history from command_history.txt in the .minecraft folder
text.fuzzy.error.not-creative: You must be in creative mode to use this feature.
text.fuzzy.messages.command-block-comman: Command sent to retrieve command block. This may fail on some servers.
